The '''Arxivers sense Fronteres''' (English: Archivists without Borders) (est. 1998) is an organization of [[archivists]] headquartered in [[Barcelona]], Spain. It facilitates volunteer efforts to [[Preservation (library and archival science)|preserve]] [[Document|documentary]] heritage, especially in [[developing countries]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.arxivers.org/home/ca-ES/qui-som/presentacio |language=ca, es |title=Qui som? Presentació AsF |publisher=Arxivers sense Fronteres |location=Barcelona |accessdate= 16 August 2017 }}</ref>
==Associated organizations== The group coordinates with branch organizations in other countries, such as:<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ica.org/en/glossary-terms-often-used-ica |title=Glossary of terms often used in ICA |publisher=[[International Council on Archives]] |location=Paris |accessdate= 16 August 2017 |quote= AsF }}</ref> * Archiveros Sin Fronteras Chile (est. 2012)<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.archiverossinfronteras.cl/?page_id=1146 |language=es |title=Quienes somos |publisher= Archiveros Sin Fronteras Chile |accessdate= 16 August 2017 }}</ref> * Archivistes sans Frontières, France (est. 2005)<ref>{{cite web |language=fr |url=http://www.archivistessansfrontieres.net/ASF-France-1 |title=Nos objectifs: ASF-France |location=Paris |publisher=Archivistes sans frontières |accessdate= 16 August 2017 }}</ref>[http://online.liverpooluniversitypress.co.uk/doi/abs/10.3828/comma.2012.1.12]
